ibliography of collections and relevant scholarly studies of yanyu.This work, the first such scholarly collection to appear since the Reverend Scarborough’s 1926 collection, will be of use not only to sinologists in a wide variety of fields, including anthropology, literature, sociology, psychology, and history, but also to non-Chinese readers interested in Chinese culture or comparative ethnolinguistic and paremiological research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 0aChinese languagevDictionariesxEnglish. 0aProverbs, ChinesevDictionaries. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Chinese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082484235240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824842352423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824842352.jpg  a978-3-11-056414-3  Hawaii eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles